  <body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
    What's your compile line and how do you use package config?<br>
    Are you building with --static without passing --static to
    pkg-config?<br>
    @HWLOC_LIBS@ should only be needed for static linking so putting it
    in Libs.private should be fine (it's returned by "pkg-config --libs
    --static hwloc").<br>
    <br>
    Brice<br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    Le 04/01/2013 23:25, Erik Schnetter a &eacute;crit&nbsp;:
    <blockquote
cite="mid:CADKQjjfj+u4X14vOg37vKDYE5Tquek4dVjqsWgn+nP6CXwdE9A@mail.gmail.com"
      type="cite">
      <div dir="ltr">Brice
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>No, this did not actually work. I was confused. It seems
          that Libs.private is ignored.</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>Instead, I am now applying the following patch:</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div>--- hwloc-1.6.orig/<a moz-do-not-send="true"
              href="http://hwloc.pc.in">hwloc.pc.in</a><span class=""
              style="white-space:pre"> </span>2012-11-12
            06:33:14.000000000 -0500</div>
          <div>+++ hwloc-1.6/<a moz-do-not-send="true"
              href="http://hwloc.pc.in">hwloc.pc.in</a><span class=""
              style="white-space:pre"> </span>2013-01-04
            10:09:54.000000000 -0500</div>
          <div>@@ -9,4 +9,4 @@</div>
          <div>&nbsp;Requires.private: @HWLOC_REQUIRES@</div>
          <div>&nbsp;Cflags: -I${includedir}</div>
          <div>-Libs: -L${libdir} -lhwloc</div>
          <div>+Libs: -L${libdir} -lhwloc @HWLOC_LIBS@</div>
          <div>&nbsp;Libs.private: @LIBS@</div>
        </div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div style="">This seems to work.</div>
        <div style=""><br>
        </div>
        <div style="">-erik</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
      </div>
